# 29. Useful Troubleshooting Commands

## Check whether Tomcat is running

```bash
ps -ef | grep tomcat
```

## Check whether port 8080 is listening

```bash
ss -tulnp | grep 8080
```

or

```bash
netstat -tulnp | grep 8080
```

## View Tomcat logs

```bash
cd /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/logs
ls -l
tail -f catalina.out
```

## Why are these commands useful?

They help you diagnose issues when:

- Tomcat is not starting
- the browser cannot connect
- the application is failing to deploy
- you see `403 Forbidden` or other errors

