# 32. Full Command Reference

## Install Java and required tools

```bash
sudo su -
apt update
apt install openjdk-21-jdk -y
java -version
apt install unzip wget -y
```

## Download and install Tomcat

```bash
cd /opt
wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-9/v9.0.106/bin/apache-tomcat-9.0.106.zip
unzip apache-tomcat-9.0.106.zip
cd /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/bin
chmod u+x *.sh
sh startup.sh
```

## Optional symbolic links

```bash
ln -s /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/bin/startup.sh /usr/bin/startTomcat
ln -s /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/bin/shutdown.sh /usr/bin/stopTomcat
```

## Edit Manager context

```bash
cd /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/webapps/manager/META-INF
vi context.xml
```

## Edit Host Manager context

```bash
cd /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/webapps/host-manager/META-INF
vi context.xml
```

## Edit users

```bash
cd /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/conf
vi tomcat-users.xml
```

## Optional port change

```bash
vi /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/conf/server.xml
```

## Restart Tomcat

```bash
cd /opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/bin
sh catalina.sh stop
sh catalina.sh start
```

## Build WAR using Maven

```bash
mvn clean package
```

## Transfer WAR using SCP

```bash
scp -i ~/Downloads/your-key.pem target/maven-web-application.war ubuntu@<server-ip>:/opt/apache-tomcat-9.0.106/webapps/
```

